            <div type="note">
                <head>Works Series</head>
                <p>Collected edition (11 vols.) of Ruskin&#x02BC;s works (prior to the Library Edition),
                    instigated by Ruskin himself and published by George Allen, 1871&#x2013;80.
                    In 1871, the first volume, <hi rend="italic">Sesame and Lilies</hi>, included an
                    &#x201C;Advertisement&#x201D; declaring Ruskin&#x02BC;s
                    opposition to current bookselling practices; however, in September 1872, the
                    &#x201C;Advertisement&#x201D; was canceled, and a cancellation slip
                    delivered a new purpose: &#x201C;The series of which this volume forms a
                    part, will contain all that I think useful of my former writings, so joined to
                    my present work as to form a consistent course of teaching&#x201D; (quoted
                    in Dearden, &#x201C;Library Edition of the Works of John
                    Ruskin,&#x201D; 51, and see 51&#x2013;52). </p>
                <p>This edition, meant to be selective, contained no early work. The order is as
                    follows: <list type="gloss">
                        <label>Volume 1,</label><item><hi rend="italic">Sesame and Lilies</hi> (with
                            1871 preface, as in <hi rend="italic">Works</hi>, 18:
                            31&#x2013;48)</item>
                        <label>Volume 2,</label><item><hi rend="italic">Munera Pulveris</hi></item>
                        <label>Volume 3,</label><item><hi rend="italic">Aratra Pentelici</hi></item>
                        <label>Volume 4,</label><item><hi rend="italic">The Eagle&#x02BC;s
                                Nest</hi></item>
                        <label>Volume 5,</label><item><hi rend="italic">Time and Tide, by Weare and
                                Tyne</hi></item>
                        <label>Volume 6,</label><item><hi rend="italic">The Crown of Wild
                            Olive</hi></item>
                        <label>Volume 7,</label><item><hi rend="italic">Ariadne
                            Florentina</hi></item>
                        <label>Volume 8,</label><item><hi rend="italic">Val
                            D&#x02BC;Arno</hi></item>
                        <label>Volume 9,</label><item><hi rend="italic">The Queen of the
                            Air</hi></item>
                        <label>Volume 10,</label><item><hi rend="italic">The Two Paths</hi></item>
                        <label>Volume 11,</label><item><hi rend="italic">A Joy for
                                Ever&#x201D;</hi></item>
                    </list>
                </p>
            </div>
